<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-04-05T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-04-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="569" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7442/35: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Canada</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Riggs</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-05T13:00:00-05:00">April 5, 1930—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:05 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>53. Department’s 38, March 29, 11 a.m. Reply to Legation’s
                            representations of March 31st received today. Department of External
                            Affairs states in note that suggested conference would be useful and
                            that date of April 10th, 1930 in New York City would be satisfactory.
                            Delegates are stated to be Mr. C. P. Edwards, Director of Radio in the
                            Department of Marine, and Major W. A. Steel, of the Department of
                            National Defense.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Riggs</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
